The control plane is the decision-making layer of Kubernetes.

Its responsibilities:
â€¢ Accept requests (from kubectl, users, CI/CD, etc.)
â€¢ Decide what should run and where
â€¢ Maintain the desired state of the cluster
â€¢ Store and manage cluster state

The control plane does not run application containers.
It only manages and coordinates.

It contains components like:
API server, scheduler, controller manager, and ETCD.

